American rapper Cardi B has deleted her Twitter account following perceived cyberbullying by trolls after she failed to attend the 64th edition of the Recording Academy’s Grammy. The mother of two took to her Twitter page to respond to trolls on the micro-blogging site before deleting her account after perceived cyberbullying and cyber-attacks on her children. “I’m deleting my Twitter but On God I hate this f–kin dumbass fan base. You got the slow dumbasses dragging my kids all-cause y’all though [sic] I was going to the Grammys and I didn’t the f–k ?” she tweeted.   Real housewives of Atlanta star, Porsha Williams spotted in…     Cubana Chief Priest’s ‘disappearance’ from…     Why I am not accepted, as a successful singer, by Davido   Continuing, she wrote: “When the f–k I hinted I was going? just f–kin stupid I can’t I needs to protect myself.” Cardi B was nominated for Best Rap Performance for Up but unfortunately lost to Baby Keem and Kendrick Lamar for their song ‘Family Ties.’ The prestigious Grammy Awards took place on April 3, 2022, at the MGM Grand Garden Arena in Las Vegas.